<dc:description>Part First. Ancient history of Silk. -- Chapter I. Spinning, dyeing, and weaving. -- Chapter II. History of the silk manufacture continued to 4th century. -- Chapter III. History of silk manufacture from the third to the sixth century. -- Chapter IV. History of silk manufacture continued from the introduction of silk-worms into Europe, A.D. 530, to the fourteenth century. -- Chapter V. Silk and golden textures of the ancients. -- Chapter VI. Silver textures, etc., of the ancients. -- Chapter VII. Description of the silk-worm, etc. -- VIII. General observations on the Chinese mode of rearing silk-worms, etc. -- Chapter IX. The spider. -- Chapter X. Fibres or silken material of the Pinna. -- Chapter XI. Fibres, or silken materials of the pine-apple. -- Chapter XII. Mallows. -- Chapter XIII. Spartum or Spanish Broom. -- Part Second. Origin and ancient history of sheep. -- Chapter I. Sheep's wool. -- Chapter II. Sheep-breeding and pastoral life of the ancients, illustrations of the Scriptures, etc. -- Chapter III. Sheep-breeding and pastoral life of the ancients, illustrations of the Scriptures, etc.  -- Chapter IV. Goats-hair. -- Chapter V. Beavers-wool. -- Chapter VI. Camels-wool and camels-hair. -- Part Third. Ancient history of the cotton manufacture. -- Chapter I. Great antiquity of the cotton manufacture in India, unrivalled skill of the Indian weaver. -- Chapter II. Spinning and weaving, marvellous skill displayed in these arts. -- Part Fourth. Ancient history of the linen manufacture. -- Chapter I. Flax. -- Chapter II. Hemp. -- Chapter III. Asbestos. -- Appendix A. On Pliny's Natural history. -- Appendix B. On the origin and manufacture of linen and cotton paper. -- Appendix C. On felt. -- Appendix D. On netting</dc:description>
